cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IT 

The paper discusses shoulder surfing as an attack vector and proposes a vulnerability metric ensemble to evaluate authentication methods' susceptibility to observational attacks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves data analysis and modeling (cs.SI), as well as cryptography (cs.CY) and information theory (cs.IT) in evaluating the effectiveness of authentication methods.
